Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.28,0:00:14.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lady Laffinty.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.07,0:00:18.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This way! Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.84,0:00:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Please wait, Lady Laffinty!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.48,0:00:30.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Oh, look at what we have here!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.98,0:00:33.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In the language of flowers,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.81,0:00:36.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the Lagrange stands for freedom, charm, and distraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.78,0:00:37.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Did you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.84,0:00:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lord Villagiulio?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.24,0:00:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.46,0:01:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was just thinking of your older brother on that ship and...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.25,0:01:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Does De Metrio always send such young men off to war?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.90,0:01:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No, your brother is an exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.02,0:01:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't like war.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.10,0:01:24.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't understand how one human can take the life of another.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.68,0:01:28.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Life is a miracle in itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.83,0:01:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You are kind, Lady Laffinty.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.77,0:01:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Your brother is in line to become the next king of Le Garite.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.19,0:01:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He may be forced into wars he has no desire to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.81,0:01:45.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That is why...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.64,0:01:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You must never change the way you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.66,0:01:52.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and be there for your brother at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.36,0:01:54.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Of course. And you too!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.92,0:01:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.22,0:02:08.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I have a dream about my enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.75,0:02:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why now, of all times?{reads better in this order but you may need to reverse if the timing doesn't work}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.76,0:02:15.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ocean sure looks beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.95,0:02:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.05,0:02:21.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would look much better if that thing wasn't there.
